The paper deals with a distributed computing problem of spreading information in a group of processors, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of randomness and fault tolerance suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The optimization of runtime and message complexity may also place the paper in the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of push-operations and lack of synchronization requirements may suggest a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
